<apex:page controller="SubscribeHelpController" action="{!findProblems}" tabStyle="SubscribeConfiguration__c" showHeader="false" standardStylesheets="true">
    
    <style>
        body {background: url('{!URLFOR("/img/in-page_clouds.png")}') top left no-repeat;}
    </style>
    <apex:form >
        <apex:pageBlock mode="maindetail">
            <apex:pageBlockSection title="About Subscribe Configuration" columns="2" collapsible="false">
                <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                    <p>The Publish and Subscribe processes work together to loosely couple two or more Sequences.</p>
                    <p>To facilitate the coupling, both the Subscribe and Publish processes must share a common Named Event.</p>
                    <p>At runtime, the Publish process directs a message to it's configured Named Event and  in turn, one or more appropriately configured Subscribe process(es) retrieve the published message from the same Named Event.</p>

                    <p><img width="480" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/SubscribeConfiguration/PubSubConfiguration.png')}" /></p>
                
                </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
                
                <apex:pageBlockSectionItem dataStyle="padding-right:10px;" >
                    <apex:pageMessages />
                </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
            </apex:pageBlockSection>


            <apex:pageBlockSection title="Configure Buttons" columns="1" collapsible="false">
                <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                    <p>To subscribe to a specific Named Event,  select that Named Event from the Event Type lookup field
                        from the Subscribe configuration page..</p>
                    <p> From the Subscribe configuration page,
                        <img style="vertical-align:middle;" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/SubscribeConfiguration/ManageEventTypes.png')}" />  takes you to a native list of all previously defined event types. To add a new event type , press the <img style="vertical-align:middle;" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/SubscribeConfiguration/NewEventType.png')}" /> button.</p>
                    <p><img style="vertical-align:middle;" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/SubscribeConfiguration/ShowStep.png')}" />  takes you to the native view of the underlying Sequence Step hosting the Subscribe process.</p>
                </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
            </apex:pageBlockSection>
            
        </apex:pageBlock>
    </apex:form>
</apex:page>